cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CS, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper deals with social media and gender inequality, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) since the paper analyzes the Facebook Gender Divide (FGD) metric, which is based on a dataset of Facebook users. The paper also discusses the impact of social media on society, which is relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper uses data analysis techniques, which could place it in cs.CS (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses gender inequality, which could place it in cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
